<TITLE>Joyce Marie Witman Steffy</TITLE>
<TEXT>
 68 of Great Falls MT formerly of East Earl PA went home to be with her Lord and Savior Monday January 23 2017 She was the wife of Richard D Steffy of Great Falls They would have celebrated their 47th wedding anniversary on March 28th Born December 15 1948 she was the oldest daughter of the late John Pin Witman and the late Loretta J Kohl Witman of New Holland PA Joyce devoted her life to public service She worked as a Licensed Practical Nurse for 30 years She started her nursing career at Ephrata Community Hospital worked the majority of her time at Zerbe Sisters Nursing Center in Narvon PA then retiring from nursing while working for Garden Spot Village assisted living in New Holland PA She also served her community as a volunteer EMT for the Fivepointville Ambulance Association for many years She was a CPR instructor and worked for Child Protect for Lancaster General Hospital in Lancaster PA After retiring from nursing she followed her grandchildren to live in Montana first in Helena and then in Great Falls There Joyce continued her public service by volunteering at the Great Falls Rescue Mission and then later working as a lunch lady at Morningside Elementary As a born again believer in Christ she had a heart and passion serving the Lord wherever she was needed Teaching children s Sunday School and Kids Church and volunteering for youth camps she had a heart for children Over the later years she was affectionately known by many kiddos as Grandma In addition to her husband she is survived by her son Donald E Steffy married to Marcy Bridegam Steffy of Great Falls Montana three brothers Leroy Witman husband of Deidre Witman of New Market New Hampshire John Witman of New Holland PA and Michael Witman of New Holland PA and one sister Nora J Witman of Manheim PA She is also survived by 5 grandchildren whom she loved and adored Joyce s celebration of life service will be held Saturday January 28 2017 at 11 00 a m at Vintage Faith Church 1801 17th Ave S Great Falls MT In lieu of flowers at the request of the family contributions can be made to the North Central Region Church of God Youth Camp Scholarship Fund P O Box 7460 Bismarck ND 585
